column5: Fun day.good eaters.was good meeting you in st charles.maybe sept we will meet again.

Lake trout opened up here in NWO yesterday so dec√¨ded to head out today.My son his girlfreind and a buddy from Manitoba joined me. As usuall first ice fishing is normally very good and the trout didnt disappoint us.My son drilled holes before i got there just from memory and was real close.We fished in 42 ft on top of a hump surround by deeper water on one side and shallow on the other.Worked out absolutly perfect as we caught a lot of trout.Didnt matter much which lure we used.The white 3 inch tube nigs and a minnow has for years been the go to but ive been using a vibrato from sebille and have found that lure will catch any species.Decent weather again today here -7 with a -15 windchill.Pretty tolerable and no need for a shelter yet.we built a fire on shore for our lunch and burned our saugages to perfection.
Nice fish, thanks for the continuing update on the season's fishing, John, this helps to make the winter pass maybe a little faster. Bill

No problem Bill.Fun for me to.only 12" of ice on Cliff Lake as compared to 16"on cedar and Edward.Talked to a freind of mine yesterday that has a trapline in the Auerobus Lake area and its only 9"there.So you have to know your ice conditions.c

I suppose it could Google, but I'll just ask here.I'm going up to Northern Ontario on a Wolf Hunt and also plan on ice fishing. We plan to hit Big Trout Lake for a couple days. Do we need a special license or stamp for trout or is a fishing license good enough?
Your good to go.nothing special needed you will need to get a outdoors card to purchase hunting and fishing licenses.good luck on your hunt.lots of wolves around.
Is Jimmy out of Pickle Lake your guide for the wolf ???? He is very good..........
Good luck, those guys are one of the (several) things hurting our moose herd.
I'm going out of Five Lakes Lodge on Gullrock. I went in 2017 as well. Ian's got a 100% success rate.And yes, hard on the Moose.
We fished some lakes east of Crow and did well.
